A permission requirements qualifies as a \"major closure.\" The rule explicitly states limited exceptions do not disqualify a broad closure. The western Tehran FIR is a major Iranian airspace region per PX-4.\n\nWhile official Iranian AIS custody would be preferable, the preponderance standard does not require perfect source chains when multiple independent sources agree on core facts. The defendant's own D-1 submission corroborates the plaintiff's evidence.\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_4499624a17d74e1da9786c79","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote"},"partialArgs":"{\"tool\": \"aar_submit_council_vote\", \"args\": ","streamIndex":0}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781911523430,"responseId":"gen-1781911523-3AHRWaUWEtDkaCgqJYPu","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}}
